properties.flavorText: We contained the evil within the astral plane. Do not tempt fate by opening it!
From here, you can see the floating platforms of the Elemental planes in the distance, and the astral Peak rises high above the center of this infinite expanse.
The shield of a fallen hero who helped seal access to these elemental planes.
Appears to have been a fighter who came on the original expedition long ago.
A small chip is missing from the side of this otherwise perfect crystal.
This halberd head bears the mark of the cloud giants.
Cool to the touch, this crystal fills you with a sense of calm.
Just looking at this crystal fills you with vigor.
Half buried, this crystal seems to have been the life force of nearby vegetation.
This giant skeleton still clutches a halberd. It appears he tried to destroy the nearby crystal and failed.
Scratch marks cover the arm and leg bones of this skeleton. Why?
This giant skeleton appears to have been crawling to the edge.
One excerpt reads: We've learned much from our time here. I would forget it all if I could.
Wrapped in a silk cloth, this crystal fills you dark foreboding whenever you gaze upon it.
A rift in reality appears, through which you can see Maeles Town in the distance.
This skeleton is still covered in tattered mage robes. It appears opening this portal was the last thing they did.
Many of the pages are missing, but it is adorned with protection runes and a sigil of the Norkian Council.
A fallen barbarian. It seems like his own axe was used to decapitate him.
Seems this bitomancer couldn't hack it.
Old beyond belief, this Norkian necromancer has been guarding access to the astral peak for many years.
This ancient crystal of water is murky from corruption.
Looking directly at the Astral Beast causes extreme confusion, and you can't quite make out what shape it is supposed to be.
These ancient beings block access to the astral beast.
Most of the water here flows in to oblivion. This waterfall, however, passes through a portal below.
